Franchises API Reference

Each ServiceStack Route will be listed with it's Return Type, which Verbs (aka Methods) are allowed to be used with it, the url path for the endpoint, notes entered by the developer in the code, a summary of the purpose of the endpoint, the data that the endpoint can take in (parameters) as well as the Return Type's properties (if an object model) and an example of how to call it in TypeScript.

AdminUpdateStatusForFranchiseOrders
POST | Returns: CEFActionResponse | Path: /Franchises/Franchise/FranchiseOrdersStatus

Returns the CEFActionResponse from updating sales order statuses

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
StatusID query int Yes Not Set!
OrderIDs query int[] Yes Not Set!

TypeScript Example

var dto = <api.AdminUpdateStatusForFranchiseOrdersDto>{
	StatusID: this.someValue1, // query 
	OrderIDs: this.someValue2, // query 
};
this.cvApi.franchises.AdminUpdateStatusForFranchiseOrders(dto).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

GetFranchiseAccounts
GET | Returns: FranchiseAccountPagedResults | Path: /Franchises/FranchiseAccounts

Use to get a list of franchise accounts

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
MasterID int? query No The Identifier of the Master Record [Optional]
MasterIDs List<int> query No The Identifiers of the Master Records [Optional]
MasterKey string query No The Custom Key of the Master Record [Optional]
MasterName string query No The Name of the Master Record [Optional]
SlaveID int? query No The Identifier of the Slave Record [Optional]
SlaveIDs List<int> query No The Identifiers of the Slave Records [Optional]
SlaveKey string query No The Custom Key of the Slave Record [Optional]
SlaveName string query No The Name of the Slave Record [Optional]
AccountID string query No Account ID For Search, Note: This will be overridden on data calls automatically
AccountIDIncludeNull bool? query No When true, allow matches to null for AccountID field
AccountKey string query No The Account Key for objects
